00:12:16,166 --> 00:12:17,500
and it wouldn't
make any difference.

242
00:12:17,583 --> 00:12:19,125
Well then, what is it?

243
00:12:19,208 --> 00:12:21,083
We have to work together.

244
00:12:21,166 --> 00:12:24,416
It's the only way to get
through the challenge.

245
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:28,375
You need to communicate
with us. Please, Aoba.

246
00:12:31,833 --> 00:12:33,166
[NOZOMI]
It's all about teamwork?

247
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:34,500
Of course.

248
00:12:34,583 --> 00:12:37,041
That's what today's hip
toss exercise was testing.

249
00:12:37,125 --> 00:12:39,208
I'm all for that,
but not in Keijo.

250
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:40,916
[NOZOMI] Yeah, I've always
thought of it as more

251
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,041
of a solo sport.

252
00:12:42,125 --> 00:12:43,625
It might seem that way.

253
00:12:43,708 --> 00:12:46,375
But behind the scenes there's
more teamwork than you'd think.

254
00:12:46,458 --> 00:12:48,291
For example, I've heard
pro Keijo players

255
00:12:48,375 --> 00:12:51,291
who work for the same agency
bounce ideas off one another.

256
00:12:51,375 --> 00:12:54,125
They discuss new tactics before
they try them out on the Land.

257
00:12:54,208 --> 00:12:56,541
Makes sense, if you ask me.

258
00:12:56,625 --> 00:12:57,958
There are a lot of
different factors

259
00:12:58,041 --> 00:12:59,291
you need to take into account

260
00:12:59,375 --> 00:13:01,458
when you're coming up with
your attack strategies.

261
00:13:01,541 --> 00:13:04,750
It would help to have another
player's input on stuff.

262
00:13:04,833 --> 00:13:06,458
It's important we communicate
with each other

263
00:13:06,541 --> 00:13:08,916
in order to get a hip
toss combo going!

264
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:11,375
[SAYAKA] That's the
only way it'll happen.

265
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:14,416
[HITOMI] Today I'll be
testing you and your team

266
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:15,833
on your hip toss.

267
00:13:15,916 --> 00:13:18,000
You've got 30 minutes to
practice and then we'll begin.

268
00:13:18,083 --> 00:13:19,583
[GIRLS]
Yes, ma'am!

269
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:22,000
I've got a special treat for the
team who comes in first place.

270
00:13:22,083 --> 00:13:24,708
They'll get to taste the most
delicious gelato in Awaji.

271
00:13:24,791 --> 00:13:26,291
[GIRLS gasp]

272
00:13:26,375 --> 00:13:27,458
Why's that special?

273
00:13:27,541 --> 00:13:29,333
And what in the heck
is gelato, anyway?

274
00:13:29,416 --> 00:13:31,916
The elite class was eating it
for breakfast, remember?

275
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,250
Oh, that stuff!

276
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:35,375
Now I'm all fired up!

277
00:13:35,458 --> 00:13:37,958
That fancy ice cream
is goin' in my face!

278
00:13:38,041 --> 00:13:39,416
[SAYAKA clears throat]

279
00:13:39,500 --> 00:13:42,791
