coming straight to me,

296
00:14:17,791 --> 00:14:20,333
but it went to Aoba instead!

297
00:14:20,416 --> 00:14:21,583
Heads up, Nozomi!

298
00:14:21,666 --> 00:14:22,708
Got my eye on it!

299
00:14:22,791 --> 00:14:24,125
[SAYAKA]
Move back a little bit!

300
00:14:24,208 --> 00:14:25,708
Okay, now to the left?

301
00:14:25,791 --> 00:14:27,291
Wait, I was wrong!

302
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:30,166
Ugh, I'm the worst leader ever.

303
00:14:30,250 --> 00:14:31,750
It's no big deal.

304
00:14:31,833 --> 00:14:34,708
It's just weird that it ended
up going right to Aoba again.

305
00:14:36,083 --> 00:14:39,916
[NOZOMI] Aoba's footprints...
Could it be?

306
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,583
[NOZOMI]
Let's try it again!

307
00:14:43,958 --> 00:14:46,416
[NON] Watch out, Miyata!
It's coming in behind you!

308
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:47,333
[SAYAKA]
Roger!

309
00:14:47,416 --> 00:14:48,791
[NOZOMI]
It's just as I thought.

310
00:14:49,875 --> 00:14:50,916
[NOZOMI gasps]

311
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,000
[SAYAKA]
I've got it!

312
00:14:52,083 --> 00:14:53,625
[NON]
Careful, Miyata! Move forward!

313
00:14:53,708 --> 00:14:54,958
[BOTH gasp]

314
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:59,875
[NOZOMI] Somehow, she knows
where the ball's gonna land!

315
00:14:59,958 --> 00:15:01,666
[NOZOMI]
How are you doing that?

316
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:03,541
You have to be our
team leader, Aoba!

317
00:15:03,625 --> 00:15:05,000
[KAZANE gasps]

318
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,125
[SAYAKA]
You honestly think she's been

319
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:09,875
reading the wind
this whole time?

320
00:15:09,958 --> 00:15:11,041
Is that possible?

321
00:15:11,125 --> 00:15:12,666
[NON]
Sounds farfetched.

322
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:14,166
There's no other explanation.

323
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:16,875
Everywhere the ball goes,
she's always right behind it.

324
00:15:16,958 --> 00:15:19,250
Well, I get why you
want her to be leader,

325
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:20,666
but she doesn't
want the job.

326
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:23,166
I don't blame her.
It's a lot of responsibility.

327
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:25,791
[NON] What're we gonna do?
We need a leader!

328
00:15:29,250 --> 00:15:31,500
Don't worry,
'cause I've got an idea!

329
00:15:32,708 --> 00:15:36,000
[HITOMI] So far our highest
combo is 35 consecutive tosses.

330
00:15:36,083 --> 00:15:38,333
Let's move on to our
last team: Room 309.

331
00:15:38,416 --> 00:15:39,416
[GIRLS]
Yes, ma'am!

332
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:41,541
Hey, Aoba!

333
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:43,583
Just do what you've
been doin', 'kay?

334
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:46,666
[HITOMI]
Begin!

335
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:48,041
[NOZOMI]
Here we go!

336
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:57,000
[NOZOMI gasps]

337
00:15:57,083 --> 00:15:59,416
Miyata the ball's headed
five diagonal meters

338
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,916
to the left of Aoba!

339
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,041
Gotcha!

340
00:16:04,083 --> 00:16:05,458
That's one!

341
00:16:08,708 --> 00:16:11,208
This way! It's two meters
to your right, Non!

342
00:16:11,291 --> 00:16:13,041
[NON]
Okie dokie!

343
00:16:13,125 --> 00:16:14,291
This is awesome.

344
00:16:14,375 --> 00:16:16,041
You know exactly where
the ball's gonna land.

345
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:18,750
I'm simply reading your signals.

346
00:16:18,833 --> 00:16:20,250
And two!

347
00:16:25,958 --> 00:16:27,500
[gasps]

348
00:16:27,583 --> 00:16:29,041
[NOZOMI]
Your ponytail.

349
00:16:29,125 --> 00:16:32,000
Whenever you notice the wind
changing, your ponytail moves!

350
00:16:32,083 --> 00:16:33,833
[NOZOMI]
Three!

351
00:16:33,916 --> 00:16:35,458
As long as I can see your hair,

352
00:16:35,541 --> 00:16:37,958
it's not hard to figure out
where the ball's going.

353
00:16:38,041 --> 00:16:40,166
Wow, that's really smart.

354
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:41,708
[NOZOMI]
Miyata!

355
00:16:41,791 --> 00:16:43,208
It's five meters to your right
and three meters behind ya!

356
00:16:43,291 --> 00:16:44,625
[SAYAKA]
I'm on it!

357
00:16:44,708 --> 00:16:45,875
[thud]

358
00:16:45,958 --> 00:16:47,458
[NOZOMI]
Your turn, Non!

359
00:16:47,541 --> 00:16:49,500
It's four meters to your left
and then take a small step back!

360
00:16:49,583 --> 00:16:50,666
[NON]
Yeppers!

361
00:16:52,375 --> 00:16:53,916
'Kay, Aoba! You're up!

362
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,958
[KAZANE gasps]

363
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:58,375
Looks like you've got
the hang of it now!

364
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:05,875
This makes 35!

365
00:17:05,958 --> 00:17:07,958
[GIRL F] They've matched
the highest team combo!

366
00:17:08,041 --> 00:17:09,750
How're they doin' it?

367
00:17:13,416 --> 00:17:17,166
Ready, Non? It's two
diagonal meters to your left!

368
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:18,083
[gasps]

369
00:17:18,166 --> 00:17:19,916
[NON]
I'm headed that way!

370
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,041
[gasps]

371
00:17:24,291 --> 00:17:25,375
[KAZANE]
No!

372
00:17:28,041 --> 00:17:29,125
[GIRLS gasp]

373
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:38,166
You're wrong! Kaminashi!

374
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:42,541
It's 15 meters back and two
meters to the left! Trust me!

375
00:17:42,625 --> 00:17:44,125
[BOTH gasp]

376
00:17:44,208 --> 00:17:46,625
[NOZOMI] I've been waiting for
you to finally speak up, Aoba!

377
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:52,250
That's 36, baby!

378
00:17:55,083 --> 00:17:57,250
She was waiting on me
to say somethin'?

379
00:17:57,333 --> 00:17:58,625
Great work today.

380
00:17:58,708 --> 00:18:00,333
[NON] Thank you! We couldn't
have done it without ya!

381
00:18:00,416 --> 00:18:03,458
[NOZOMI] We did it, guys!
We're the top team!

382
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:05,000
Whoops, didn't mean
to knock you over!

383
00:18:05,083 --> 00:18:06,250
Guess you're the
clumsy one not me!

384
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:07,708
I don't know my own strength!

385
00:18:09,458 --> 00:18:10,625
[NOZOMI]
What?

386
00:18:10,708 --> 00:18:12,958
You were embarrassed of
your Hiroshima accent?

387
00:18:13,041 --> 00:18:14,333
[KAZANE]
Yeah, it may seem silly,

388
00:18:14,416 --> 00:18:16,250
but on the first day you said--

389
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:18,916
Wow, Non, your accent's the
funniest thing I've ever heard!

390
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,750
[NOZOMI laughs]

391
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:23,250
You stopped talking because you
thought she'd make fun of you?

392
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:25,375
In other words,
this is all your fault.

393
00:18:25,458 --> 00:18:27,125
[NOZOMI]
Guess I should watch what I say.

394
00:18:27,208 --> 00:18:28,583
I'm really sorry, y'all.

395
00:18:28,666 --> 00:18:30,833
[NOZOMI] If anyone should
apologize it's me!

396
00:18:30,916 --> 00:18:33,541
Sorry. Um, "y'all."

397
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:36,875
[SAYAKA] You can be so
insensitive sometimes.

398
00:18:36,958 --> 00:18:38,916
[NOZOMI] It's finally
time for Land class!

399
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:41,500
I've been waiting for this day!

400
00:18:41,583 --> 00:18:44,416
It feels like it's been forever
since I've been on a Land!

401
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,458
[NOZOMI grunts]

402
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:47,375
Uh. What do you
think you're doing?

403
00:18:47,458 --> 00:18:49,791
Nothing. I just
noticed your butt.

404
00:18:49,875 --> 00:18:51,708
It looked so firm
I had to touch it.

405
00:18:51,791 --> 00:18:54,458
Whoa, what's going on over here?
